cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use pyBmodes in academic work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "pyBmodes — Python finite-element library for wind turbine blade and tower modal analysis"
abstract: >-
  pyBmodes is a pure-Python finite-element library for wind turbine
  blade and tower modal analysis. It reads OpenFAST / ElastoDyn /
  SubDyn / HydroDyn / MoorDyn decks, BModes .bmi decks, and WISDEM /
  WindIO ontology YAML files; solves the coupled flap-lag-torsion-
  axial vibration modes with a 15-DOF Bernoulli-Euler beam element;
  and emits ElastoDyn-compatible mode-shape polynomials, MAC-tracked
  Campbell diagrams, and bundled reports. Validated against the
  BModes Fortran reference solver on six benchmark cases (NREL 5MW
  land + OC3 monopile + OC3 Hywind floating spar, IEA-3.4-130-RWT,
  BModes CertTest 03/04) to better than 0.01 % on every comparison.
